# ============================================================
# Haley Yachts Vendor Database - Staff password realm
# ============================================================
# Everything under /vendors/ is staff-only. Access is gated by a
# cPanel Directory Privacy password realm SEPARATE from /admin/.
# That separation is intentional: staff users added here can use the
# vendor directory but can NEVER reach the admin lists endpoint in
# /admin/, which is a different realm with its own users.
#
# SETUP (do this once, on the GoDaddy server - see vendors/README-SETUP.md):
#   1. In cPanel, open "Directory Privacy" (a.k.a. "Password Protect
#      Directories").
#   2. Browse to the /vendors/ folder under public_html.
#   3. Check "Password protect this directory" and name it something
#      like "Haley Yachts Vendors".
#   4. Add one user per staff member with a strong password. cPanel
#      writes the .htpasswd file and appends the cp:ppd block below.
#
# The cp:ppd block (if present below) is managed by cPanel's Directory
# Privacy tool. Do NOT hand-edit it. Re-running Directory Privacy
# regenerates it.
#
# CUTOVER NOTE: the in-app login (login.html, auth.php, reset.html) now gates
# this area at the application layer. The app page (index.php) redirects
# unauthenticated visitors to login.html server-side, and the data API
# (api/api.php) returns 401 to anyone without a session. Once you remove the
# cPanel Directory Privacy realm from /vendors/ (the documented final step in
# README-SETUP.md), login.html / auth.php / reset.html become publicly
# reachable ON PURPOSE - they have to be, so a logged-out user can sign in or
# reset a password. Do NOT re-add a directory-wide password on top of them.
# Until that removal, the cp:ppd block below still password-gates everything.
# ============================================================

# ----- Deny direct access to sensitive files -----
<FilesMatch "^\.(htaccess|htpasswd)$">
    Require all denied
</FilesMatch>

# ----- No directory listing -----
Options -Indexes

# ============================================================
# "WE HAVE MOVED" NOTICE (added 2026-07)
# ============================================================
# This is the OLD pre-migration deployment. The app has moved to
# owyg.yachtbrokersupport.com. Rather than delete this app or its data (a
# staff member may still have data here), we serve a friendly notice page
# (moved.html) at the ENTRY POINTS so anyone landing here is pointed at the
# new app. The underlying app files, the SQLite database, and uploads/docs
# are LEFT IN PLACE and untouched - only the entry pages are intercepted.
#
# The directory index now shows the notice, and the app entry pages
# (login/index/suite/change-password/reset, both .php and legacy .html) are
# rewritten to moved.html. Data paths (api/, pocket/uploads/, *.sqlite) are
# NOT matched, so nothing about the stored data is affected.
DirectoryIndex moved.html

<IfModule mod_rewrite.c>
    RewriteEngine On
    # Never rewrite the notice page itself (prevents a loop).
    RewriteCond %{REQUEST_URI} !/moved\.html$ [NC]
    # Intercept only the app entry pages, at this directory level only.
    RewriteRule ^(login|index|suite|change-password|reset)\.(php|html)$ moved.html [L]
</IfModule>
